.TH "Document.selectionchange_event" "JS" "April 7, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Document.selectionchange_event \- Document: selectionchange event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]selectionchange\f[B]\f[R] event of the Selection API is
fired when the current \f[CR]Selection\f[R] of a \f[CR]Document\f[R] is
changed.
.PP
This event is not cancelable and does not bubble.
.PP
The event can be handled by adding an event listener for
\f[CR]selectionchange\f[R] or using the \f[CR]onselectionchange\f[R]
event handler.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This event is not quite the same as the
\f[CR]selectionchange\f[R] events fired when the text selection in an
\f[CR]<input>\f[R] or \f[CR]<textarea>\f[R] element is changed.
See \f[CR]HTMLInputElement.selectionchange_event\f[R] for more details.
.RE
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\[dq]selectionchange\[dq], (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {});

onselectionchange = (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {};
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[I]// addEventListener version\f[R]
document.addEventListener(\[dq]selectionchange\[dq], () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(document.getSelection());
});

\f[I]// onselectionchange version\f[R]
document.onselectionchange = () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(document.getSelection());
};
.EE
